snippet.textDisplay:
Hi brad,
Since we’re all in lock down, and lots of people will be dedicating this time to learning new things, I thought it’d be awesome for you to do a mini series of 5-10 minute videos, each one dedicated to the proper ways to use a tool, or product.
Example; “how to use mouse” what it does, how to apply it, which hair types would benefit from it & an example of a hair style styled with it.
A video on heat protectant would be great, I’m never sure if it’s actually working or not? Or what ingredients I should be looking for when choosing one? Or what’s the best way to apply it?

I know it sounds simple, but lots of girls that come here are hair novices & want to learn how to style their hair better. I think this series would be really popular!
Thanks for reading my comment & listening to my idea ❤️
snippet.textOriginal:
Hi brad, 
Since we’re all in lock down, and lots of people will be dedicating this time to learning new things, I thought it’d be awesome for you to do a mini series of 5-10 minute videos, each one dedicated to the proper ways to use a tool, or product. 
Example; “how to use mouse” what it does, how to apply it, which hair types would benefit from it & an example of a hair style styled with it. 
A video on heat protectant would be great, I’m never sure if it’s actually working or not? Or what ingredients I should be looking for when choosing one? Or what’s the best way to apply it? 

I know it sounds simple, but lots of girls that come here are hair novices & want to learn how to style their hair better. I think this series would be really popular! 
Thanks for reading my comment & listening to my idea ❤️

snippet.textDisplay: I bleached my whole head in a salon. My hair was worse than straw and stuck to itself. I found that washing it once a week or so helped to repair it because that allowed time for my natural oils to work. It got somewhat better over time but never got out of the straw phase. Ended up having to chop it and just start over.
